==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hematite
<hw>Hem"a*tite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>haematites</ets>, Gr. <?/ bloodlike, fr. <grk>a"i^ma</grk>,
<grk>a"i`matos</grk>, blood.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>An important
ore of iron, the sesquioxide, so called because of the red color of the
powder. It occurs in splendent rhombohedral crystals, and in massive and
earthy forms; -- the last called red ocher. Called also
<altname>specular iron</altname>, <altname>oligist iron</altname>,
<altname>rhombohedral iron ore</altname>, and
<altname>bloodstone</altname>. See <cref>Brown hematite</cref>, under
<er>Brown</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hematitic</ent>⟦br⟧
